**V. TUNING STEP 3

Compute the Relational Curvature (Contextual Inconsistency)**

The gauge curvature is:

F_A = \dot A + A^2

High curvature = incompatible problem formulations.

Low curvature = integrated mathematical structure.

In practice:
	•	Navier–Stokes + Yang–Mills share low-curvature structures (energy inequalities, Sobolev embeddings).
	•	Riemann + BSD have low-curvature coupling through L-functions.
	•	P vs NP has high curvature with analytic number theory = hard to unify directly.

So the curvature tensor is a map of which strings can be harmonized.

This tells you:

Which problems can be tuned together and which should be isolated.

The Millennium Guitar becomes a structural diagnostic tool.

⸻

